name: Emigrant General Store
directions: In the back, behind the wall of rental movies and next to the small produce section.
comment: Single room bathroom. The room is a bit small, not really accessible for larger wheelchairs. Also, as this is one of the only gas stations in a long distance between Livingston and Gardiner/Yellowstone, it tends to be very busy during the summer.

name: Wright State University Lake Campus
directions: In Dwyer Hall in the administrative wing (walk to your right side just past the front desk and it's the first door on the left).

name: Wright State University Lake Campus
directions: In Trenary Hall by the break room. Walk in through the Business Enterprise Center Entrance.

name: Chocolate Coffee
directions: In the back
comment: You have to be a "paying customer"

name: Pain Quotidien
directions: Back of the establishment

name: Pain Quotidien
directions: Back of the establishment

name: Higglands Diva Espresso
directions: Towards the back on the right-hand side
comment: Supposed to be for customers only, but if you look presentable it ask if you can use it, no one will bother you.

name: Spar
directions: Back left corner of the store

name: Kiwis Brew Bar
directions: Upstairs (but this is normally only open if they are screening a sports match or something : S)

name: Starbucks
directions: Single stall unisex in the back of the store to the right, across from registers.
comment: You do not need to be a paying customer, free for all to use.

name: Taurus Crafts
directions: There's some cubicles by the cafe and some more in a passage near the florist. All unisex/ neutral!
comment: Might have to act like you're browsing as it's a craft centre, but people don't really bat an eyelid about who uses the loos.

name: Wanderlust Tattoo
directions: Rear of the studio
comment: Just ask at the front desk and you'll be directed.

name: Douglas Houghton Hall
directions: Next to front desk.

name: Hillside Place
directions: 2x across from room 107/sauna

name: Great Lakes Research Center
directions: 1st floor next to west stairwell.

name: McNair Hall
directions:
West McNair: In-between lounge/game room, across from stairwell
East McNair: 2x near lounge

name: Bridges USA
directions: In the back with the cubicles.
comment: You have to be a student in one of their programs or attending one of their events.

name: Hallet Cove Railway Station
directions: It's on the platform for the train.

name: Monarto Zoo
directions: By the Chimpanzee exhibit. On the viewing platform.
comment: You have to be inside the zoo. (You have to pay to get in.)

name: Organic Delicious Cafe
directions: Through door at the back and downstairs
comment: Would probably have to buy something (cafe is too small to sneak in unnoticed)

name: Anodyne Coffee
directions: To the left of the ordering counter

name: Woodburn Walmart
directions: In the very back of the store by pets and shoes
comment: "Family" bathroom but free to use for anyone. They close the backrestrooms at 9pm though

name: United Art and Education
directions: Go straight from the entrance until you hit Clearance, it'll be in a hall to your right. You can see the sign from the entrance.
comment: There are two bathrooms, if the first door is shut or locked then try the second one next to the employees only room at the end of the hall. The first one has a baby changing station.

name: University of Oregon
directions: A good amount of Gender neutral bathrooms on the UO campus. They are all listed on a map on the UO's website under maps>> interactive map>> search gender inclusive restroom.
comment: Often harder to find than gendered restrooms, but university staff know they exist and asking at a desk (if you feel safe enough to do so) can help you find them if the map isn't clear.

name: The Union of UEA students
street: Union House, The University of East Anglia
directions:
There are three gender neutral toilets in the Union building:
One downstairs in the Red Bar 
One at the back of the Hive by the advice centre
One in the LCR entrance hall
comment: All are accessible during LCR nights and at least two can be accessed during concert events.

name: Crab House at Pier 39
directions: Towards the entry

name: Taco Bell
directions: inside, all the way to the right.
comment: ask for the key

name: Kroger
directions: When entering the store, bathroom on the far left by Starbucks not the gendered ones by the pharmacy.

name: Caf√© La Tartine
directions: In the back on the left

name: Speedway
directions: Turn to the right after entering the store, and you can't miss them.
comment: The store is open 24/7 and you don't need to make a purchase to use the bathroom facilities.

name: Whole Foods
directions: Inside the side entrance, by the bar

name: SFMOMA
directions: There are two single-stall all-gender restrooms on the third floor, towards the back of the gallery by the study center. They are indicated on the museum map by a toilet logo, as opposed to the gendered logos for other restrooms in the building.
comment: You must have a ticket to the museum to access this area.

name: College Hill Pizza Pub
directions: To the right, on the way to the kitchen.
comment: Open to everyone. You don't have to be a customer.

name: SHOP 'n SAVE Fresh
directions: To the right just as you enter, go past deli counter on the right and the deli on the left and keep walking back. Pass drinking fountains and the bathrooms are back there.
comment: There is a male and female gendered restroom. The bathrooms are the size of a large closet, completely single.

name: Apache Mall
directions: Family bathroom - enter through the Food Court entrance, then stay to the right past Barnes and Noble. Turn right into the bathroom hallway, where the family bathroom will be on the left.

name: Walmart Supercenter
directions: All the way in the back, where one might go to put items on layaway, right between electronics section and toy section.

name: The Taphouse
directions: There are two sets of single occupancy gendered restrooms - one pair on the first floor past the bar and by the stairs, and another on either side once you go up the stairs.
comment: This is a bar, so you must be 21+ and I recommend getting a drink in order to be a "paying customer." They might stop you otherwise.

name: Chipotle
directions: In the back, in a hallway on the far right side of the building when you enter
comment: Usually VERY crowded, so just be aware.

name: Left Hand Park
directions: It is in a building near the parking lot, with the drinking fountain.
comment: its a park restroom

name: Carleton College
directions: Enter through main "Sayles Hill" door and go straight. Turn left to go towards the Great Hall, then turn right down the following hallway running parallel to the Hall. Make a final left and there will be a gender neutral bathroom right there!
comment: Carleton makes an effort to be accepting of all gender identities but it can still be stressful so this one's a good option just in case.

name: Jewel Osco
directions: In the Starbucks

name: New Madison public library
directions: Left from back door

name: Thyme and Again Creative Catering and Cafe
Bridgehead
comment: You have to ask for the key at the cash

name: Waldo pizza
directions: Inside, left around the host station, past the bar on the left.

name: Tea drops
comment: Have to be a customer

name: St Luke's hospital
directions: Near the cafeteria
comment: Both gendered single stall and a unisex single stall

name: Hoyts Metro
directions:
Escalator beside the entrance to Centreplace food court takes you up to the cinema, or use the lift (same one that services the carparks, iirc) for wheelchair access.
Toilets are immediately behind where the escalator comes out, so turn around and they should be obvious.
comment: I've come here as a paying customer and not; it's been fine either way, though I imagine they prefer you buy something. These are some of the nicest toilets I've ever been to in Hamilton!

name: Public Toilet
directions: It's a public toilet, so unless it gets repainted after this entry it's probably beige with a green roof and glowing lights on the front.
comment: Public toilet, so is liable to be gross. Suggest you only use it in emergency. Safe enough during the day, but avoid it at night - it's on the drunk-assholes-wander-here route and some bad stuff has happened there at night.

name: Brew
comment: Just go in and use whenever.

name: Tui Medical - Victoria St
directions: You can enter through Neville Kane pharmacy or their main door on the other side; toilets are down behind the reception counter and to the right - they're labelled, so should be easy to spot!
comment:
Open weekdays only 9am to 12pm and 1pm to 4pm Monday to Friday. Tell the receptionist that you need the toilet as you go in and you shouldn't have any hassle.
For the most part they're pretty trans-friendly, though some of the nurses are prone to pronoun slips. If you're just having an emergency and you don't actually need to see a doctor they'll still be ok with you using the toilet.

name: Mamaroneck Public Library District
directions: Two on the 2nd floor (children's room), one on the lower level in the hallway behind the community room.
comment: The larger of the children's room rest rooms has a changing table.

name: Centreplace Hamilton
directions: All of the toilets are near the lift from the in-building carpark; alternately if you're coming from outside it's in the narrow bit between the food court and the rest of the building. There's a long corridor and at the end are bog-standard gendered toilets, but earlier along the corridor on the right is an accessible unisex toilet. There's also a parents' room, if you have a kid!
comment: It's a shopping centre, so these loos are for everyone.

name: Westfield Trumbull Mall
directions: Family restroom across from cheesecake factory, next to Ten restaurant

name: Burger King Ward St
directions: Through the front door and to the right by the drink machines.
comment:
Bathrooms are labelled gendered though in practice anyone uses any, so no-one'll really care unless they're busting!
They prefer you buy something, but I've used them without buying things with no trouble. And if you turn up during rush hour (lunch, school ending, work ending) there's usually a big enough crowd that they don't care.

name: The Creative Crust
directions: Next to the Markethouse entrance, only door in the business.
comment: Free to the public. Small business owners who mind their own business so long as you don't interfere with theirs.

name: Dublin Roasters
directions: After entering business, turn right into adjacent room, bathrooms are down hallway. 2 gender neutral bathrooms in an extremely LGBT- welcoming and safe business.

name: Starbucks
comment: Ask an employee for the bathroom key

name: E. P. Foster Library
directions: It's to your left when you walk in through the front entrance
comment: There's a water fountain near it too

name: Kroger
directions: Walk in the front, take a left. It's around the pharmacy/Drug&GM.
comment: It's between the "standard" gendered bathroom doors, and features a vacancy/occupied sign on the lock, which is nice. During the night, the light switch can be finicky. It's very clean and always has enough toilet paper. I wouldn't hold my breath about having paper towels though, those are always a gamble in our store.

name: Peet's Coffee and Tea
directions: On the left hand side of the cash registers.
comment:
Single use bathrooms marked for binary genders but are both exactly the same and many CIS customers use either/or
Nobody cares if you pay or not.

name: East Hampton High School
directions: Near the cafeteria, next to the Women's Faculty Restroom

name: Insomnia Cookies
directions: Walk in the door, bathroom is down a short hallway on the left.
comment: No need to buy anything, you can just come in to use the bathroom.

name: Insomnia Cookies
directions: Walk in the door, it'll be down a short hallway on your left.
comment: No need to buy anything or even browse, you can just walk in to use the bathroom.  No questions asked.

name: The public Theater
directions: First floor, the receptionists will happily tell you where it is
comment: Public space for everyone

name: Mesa Community College
directions: Two family restrooms on both floors of the Physical Sciences building. (Large building with Planetarium south of library.) Left of gendered restrooms.
comment: Elevator available.

name: MLA Jane Shin's Constituency Office
comment: Ask at front desk - mention that you're looking for a Refuge Restroom as they aren't technically public

name: Potbelly's
directions: Near side entrance/ drink machines
comment: Both "mens and womens" bathrooms are one personal rooms with a lock, staff are friendly and bathrooms are nice

name: Lucky Otter
directions: two single stall restrooms (gendered, though that is rumored to be changing soon) in the back left of the front dining area
comment: don't worry about being a paying customer, the staff is friendly and wont have a problem with you just going in and using the restroom.

name: Sydenham High School
directions: In the new addition, not really near the main gym or anything useful. Not marked super well, look for the lit "in use" sign in the hallway.

name: Tim Hortons (Innovation Drive)
comment: Clean. Gendered washrooms with stalls are also available and are safe to use as well.

name: Guthrie Memorial Library
directions: On the first floor by the front desk and computer area
comment: You have to go to the front desk and ask for the key

name: Kowalski's Market
directions: Go in the front doors, and walk straight ahead, past the checkouts to the deli. Follow the deli cases to the back of the store. Walk through the set of double doors. Male and female bathrooms will be on your right.

name: (HACC) Harrisburg Area Community College - Gettysburg Campus
directions: In the back hallway near the "environmentally friendly" backyard, right around the corner from a women's bathroom. Unisex bathroom has a lock on the door as well as a stall, two sinks, a chair, trashcan, and shelves inside the lockable room.
comment: Act like you're a student, you should be fine

name: Toppers Pizza
directions: Past the TVs
comment: If you don't want to order food, just politely ask if you can use the bathroom.

name: Walmart Supercenter
directions: At the front of the store, near the registers

name: Chipotle Mexican Grill
directions: In the left side hallway
comment: Fast food restaurant, so you can just walk in

name: Westlake High School
directions: Straight through rotunda, first door past the ticket booth on the right
comment: Must be high school student or staff, unless during a special event.

name: Nordstrom Valley Fair
directions: Third floor by the elevators

name: BJ's Wholesale Club
directions: If you enter from the right it is straight down past the registers and member services desk. It's a large unisex bathroom and is handicap accessible.
comment: You do not have to have a membership to enter the club, but there is a Front Door greeter who will greet you. Just ask them where the restrooms are and they will helpfully point them out for you.

name: Bridgehead Roastery
directions: Two bathrooms in the back, behind the community table.

name: Jeni's Splendid Ice Creams
directions: in the back to the left

name: Kenapocomocha
directions: Ramp on the side of building for handicapped individuals. Friendly staff and single stall restroom
comment: No need to buy anything. Although the food is all local and organic. Lovely staff.

name: Brown family home
directions: Knock on my door, and we will definitely let you come in to pee.  We have two full bathrooms.  Shower if you need to.
comment: This is a house in the middle of the woods.  If you are here, you are probably lost.

name: Leo Hayes High School
directions: There are 3 gender neutral single stalled bathrooms. One in the staff room, left when you enter the front doors and 2 in downstairs D wing when you first enter by the cafeteria. Looks like a classroom but it isn't. All 3 washrooms should be labeled with a sign.
comment: If you're nervous about going in the staff room one, don't be. No teachers will yell at you.
